-- Syndicate Bank Said to Meet Investors Before 5 Billion Rupee Sale of Bonds
-- B y   S u p r o t i p   G h o s h
-- 2010-10-05T04:23:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-05/syndicate-bank-said-to-meet-investors-before-5-billion-rupee-sale-of-bonds.html
Syndicate Bank, a government-
controlled Indian lender, met investors ahead of a planned sale
of bonds, according to two people familiar with the matter.  The Bangalore-based borrower may raise more than 5 billion
rupees ($112 million) and use proceeds to strengthen its capital
base, said the people, who asked not to be identified as the
details are private.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Suprotip Ghosh in Mumbai 
 sghosh47@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Will McSheehy at   wmcsheehy@bloomberg.net . 